text: Eugenia mozomboensis is a species of plant in the family Myrtaceae. It is endemic to Veracruz state, in eastern Mexico. It is an Endangered species, threatened by habitat loss. ==References== mozomboensis Category:Endemic flora of Mexico Category:Flora of Veracruz Category:Endangered biota of Mexico Category:Endangered flora of North America Category:Trees of Veracruz Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
